            "languageId": "markdown",
            "value": "# Lesson 5: Create Map Filter ",
            "output": [],
            "executionSummary": {}
        },
        {
            "kind": 1,
            "languageId": "markdown",
            "value": "In this lesson, we’ll create our first component and add it to the page `WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx`. This component allows users to select zero, one, or many `WindTurbine` IDs, which we'll later use to filter the `WindTurbine`s that appear on the map.",
            "output": [],
            "executionSummary": {}
        },
        {
            "kind": 1,
            "languageId": "markdown",
            "value": "### Learning Objectives",
            "output": [],
            "executionSummary": {}
        },
        {
            "kind": 1,
            "languageId": "markdown",
            "value": "After completing this lesson, you will be able to:\n- Create a reusable React component.\n- Pass data to components using props.\n- Import and render components in parent pages.",
            "output": [],
            "executionSummary": {}
        },
        {
            "kind": 1,
            "languageId": "markdown",
