        },
        {
            "kind": 1,
            "languageId": "markdown",
            "value": "## Part 1: Create the `WindTurbineFilter` component\n\n**Steps**:\n1. Create a new file: `ui/c3/src/components/WindTurbineFilter.tsx`. This component:\n    - Renders a dropdown with checkboxes for each `WindTurbine` ID. \n    - When a user selects/deselects turbines, the `selectedTurbines` state updates.\n    - Supports multi-select (zero, one, or many `WindTurbine`s can be selected).\n    - Later, we'll use this selection to filter markers on the map.\n\n2. Copy and paste the following code into that file.\n\n\n**Code:**",
            "output": [],
            "executionSummary": {}
        },
        {
            "kind": 2,
            "languageId": "typescriptreact",
            "value": "/*\n  WindTurbineFilter.tsx\n\n  This component provides a filter interface for selecting wind turbines from a dropdown menu.\n  It uses Material-UI components for the dropdown and checkboxes, and maintains the selected turbines in its state.\n*/\n\nimport React from 'react';\nimport '@c3/ui/WindTurbine.scss';\nimport { Select } from '@mui/material';\n\ninterface WindTurbineFilterProps {\n  turbines: WindTurbine[];\n}\n\nconst WindTurbineFilter: React.FC<WindTurbineFilterProps> = ({ turbines }) => {\n \n  return (\n    <>\n      <div className=\"filter-container\">\n        {/* Filter Header */}\n        <div className=\"filter-header\">\n          <h3 className=\"filter-title\">Wind Turbine Filter</h3>\n        </div>\n\n        {/* Dropdown Selection */}\n        <div className=\"filter-dropdown-section\">\n          <label className=\"filter-label\">Select Wind Turbine:</label>\n\n          <Select\n            labelId=\"turbine-select-label\"\n            multiple\n          />\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </>\n  );\n};\n\nexport default WindTurbineFilter;\n",
            "output": [],
            "executionSummary": {}
        },
        {
            "kind": 1,
            "languageId": "markdown",
            "value": "---",
            "output": [],
            "executionSummary": {}
        },
        {
            "kind": 1,
            "languageId": "markdown",
            "value": "## Part 2: Add the `WindTurbine` filter component to the home page\n\nAdd the following import statement to the top of <a href=\"../../ui/c3/src/customInstances/WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx\"><code>WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx</code></a>:",
            "output": [],
            "executionSummary": {}
        },
        {
            "kind": 2,
            "languageId": "typescriptreact",
            "value": "/*\n    WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx\n*/\n\n// Other import statements in the project\nimport WindTurbineFilter from '@c3/app/ui/src/components/WindTurbineFilter';\n\n// const WindTurbineHomePage: React.FC = () => {\n//      ...\n// }",
            "output": [],
            "executionSummary": {}
        },
        {
            "kind": 1,
            "languageId": "markdown",
            "value": "Now we want to include the `WindTurbineFilter.tsx` component in the return statement. We will be passing the `turbines` state as the `turbines` prop for the component:",
            "output": [],
            "executionSummary": {}
        },
        {
            "kind": 2,
            "languageId": "typescriptreact",
            "value": "/*\n      WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx\n*/\n\n// <MapContainer>\n      <WindTurbineFilter turbines={turbines} />\n//    <ZoomControl>\n// </MapContainer>",
            "output": [],
            "executionSummary": {}
        },
        {
            "kind": 1,
            "languageId": "markdown",
            "value": "---",
            "output": [],
            "executionSummary": {}
        },
        {
            "kind": 1,
            "languageId": "markdown",
            "value": "## Part 3: Verify the component \n\n**Steps**:\n1. Save your changes and refresh the browser.\n2. You should see a \"Wind Turbine Filter\" dropdown above the map.\n3. Click the dropdown. **You should see an empty dropdown. This is expected**\n\nYour page should match the following image:\n\n<img src=\"../../src/doc/img/lesson-5/map-filter.png\" width=\"750px\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">",
            "output": [],
            "executionSummary": {}
        },
        {
            "kind": 1,
            "languageId": "markdown",
            "value": "-----",
            "output": [],
            "executionSummary": {}
        },
        {
            "kind": 1,
            "languageId": "markdown",
            "value": "### Summary\nYou built a reusable `WindTurbineFilter` component and rendered it on the home page.",
            "output": [],
            "executionSummary": {}
